# Placeholder Image: Project Dependency Diagram

This is a placeholder for a diagram showing:

## Visual Content Needed:
- DDD layer dependency flow diagram
- Four layers: Presentation, Application, Infrastructure, Domain
- Arrows showing allowed dependencies
- Clear indication that Domain has NO dependencies

## Suggested Diagram Content:

```
┌─────────────────┐
│  Presentation   │ (WPF, ViewModels, Views)
│   Layer         │
└────────┬────────┘
         │
         ├──────────────────┐
         │                  │
         ▼                  ▼
┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐
│  Application    │  │ Infrastructure  │
│    Layer        │  │     Layer       │
└────────┬────────┘  └────────┬────────┘
         │                    │
         │                    │
         └──────────┬─────────┘
                    ▼
            ┌─────────────────┐
            │     Domain      │ ◄── NO DEPENDENCIES
            │      Layer      │     (Pure business logic)
            └─────────────────┘
```

## Key Annotations to Include:
1. Presentation → Application (Uses application services)
2. Presentation → Infrastructure (Direct access to implementations)
3. Application → Domain (Uses domain entities and interfaces)
4. Infrastructure → Domain (Implements domain interfaces)
5. Domain → (nothing) - Dependency-free core

